metadata.name: Tribute to Frida
metadata.description:
A letter to Frida:

"For the world who didnâ€™t understand you,
A lot of women after you, salute you.
Flowers upon flowers you sow, 
As your body rots in the soil.
For the world that remains violent,
You have painted so much of your pain.
For then we see flowers as I walk down,
on this lonely path.

But today,
I love you more than my own skin."

Archival ink on Hahnemuhle German Etching paper print will be offered to primary collector.
